    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Reviving this issue as we are going through all the issues. We already had this issue in the helper, and it now provides all the facets even if they are returned in the list of facets but they are selected. The only problem is that by default in instantsearch.js the sort (of the refinement list) does not use isRefined as the first sort argument. Therefore even if it is refined and present in the list of facets, it is not considered relevant.\n\nHere is an example that fixes the issue for the `materials` facet on the amazing/ecommerce sample:\n\n``` js\nsearch.addWidget(\n  instantsearch.widgets.refinementList({\n    container: '#materials',\n    attributeName: 'materials',\n    operator: 'or',\n    limit: 10,\n    sortBy: ['isRefined', 'count:desc', 'name:asc'],\n    templates: {\n      item: facetTemplateCheckbox,\n      header: '<div class=\"facet-title\">Materials</div class=\"facet-title\">'\n    }\n  })\n);\n```\n\nNote the new sort that I used: `sortBy: ['isRefined', 'count:desc', 'name:asc']` It is clearly not obvious in the documentation and be a recipe.\n\nI did a small screencast to show you what is my understanding of the correct behavior. Let me know @Jerskouille @vvo \n\n![facets-hidden](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/393765/15925519/c4cae22c-2e37-11e6-9d22-5627653269f4.gif)\n",
